=begin
If we list all the natural numbers below 10 that are multiples of 3 or 5,
we get 3, 5, 6, and 9. The sum of these multiples is 23.

Find the sum of all the multiples of 3 or 5 below 1000.
=end

total = 0
	for i in 1...1000
		if i%3 == 0 or i%5 == 0
		array = [i]
		#puts "#{array}" (This will show me all the values multiple by 3 and 5. Erase # for values to print.

			array.each do |x|
			total += x

		end
	end
end
puts "The sum of the multiples below 1000 is #{total}"

